{
  "texts": [
    "The release of GPT3 in November of 2022 by OpenAI constituted a bellwether for humanity, heralding a new age of powerful and easily accessible generative Artificial Intelligence (AI).",
    "Capturing widespread public and media attention (e.g.",
    "Mollman, 2023; Roose, 2023; Wingard, 2023), ChatGPT (OpenAI, 2023) could now provide extended text responses to a wide variety of natural language prompts that often passed for intelligent and informed human prose.",
    "Amongst those media reports, there were various opinions about the possible implications of generative AI for education, and what teachers might think, but none of these were based on research evidence.",
    "Understanding educator beliefs about how teaching and assessment will need to change in response to generative AI is important, because it underpins the sorts of changes that we can expect to see in educational institutions around the world."
  ]
}